                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/143</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-04T17:00:00-05:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to the Legation’s telegram of April 30, noon. Vote on Senate reversed
                    and adopted almost unanimously today on orders from Tinoco, inspired by belief,
                    for which Legation not responsible <pb facs="0489" n="323" xml:id="pg_323"/>
                    that such action will help obtain recognition. However objections enumerated in
                    telegram referred to one and two cannot and objections three and four not
                    proposed to be remedied.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
